<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,311,635,661]" box="[189,311,635,661]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,311,635,661]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,311,635,661]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1401,682,884]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Martínez &amp; Bonaldo, 2022" authorityName="Sánchez-Ruiz &amp; Martínez &amp; Bonaldo" authorityYear="2022" box="[306,404,682,709]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huila" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[306,404,682,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. huila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[412,504,683,709]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1994" box="[737,865,683,709]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramo">
<emphasis box="[737,865,683,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. paramo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a large cymbium that is more than twice as long as the tibia length, and by a similar poorly pronounced dorsal tubercle on the palpal femur (
<figureCitation box="[198,318,752,779]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 3H–J</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by having a anteriorly directed embolar base (
<figureCitation box="[1169,1295,752,779]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 4D–F</figureCitation>
), instead posteriorly directed as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1994" box="[500,629,788,814]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramo">
<emphasis box="[500,629,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. paramo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Platnick N. I." box="[698,881,788,814]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref7090" refString="Platnick N. I. 1994 a. A revision of the spider genus Caponina (Araneae, Caponiidae). American Museum Novitates 3100: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1994">Platnick 1994a</bibRefCitation>
: figs 39–41). Additionally, the embolus tip is larger than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1994" box="[446,575,823,849]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Caponina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramo">
<emphasis box="[446,575,823,849]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">C. paramo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, presenting a median expansion, widening tip and enlarged opening (
<figureCitation box="[197,321,858,884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Figs 3H–J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[333,405,858,884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">4D–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
