<typeStatus box="[314,421,605,631]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">holotype</typeStatus>
, IAvH-I 3761)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1400,605,738]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">
COLORATION. Carapace yellowish-orange (
<figureCitation box="[683,781,640,667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Figs 3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[795,835,640,667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. A–B. Caponina alejandroi sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3747). A. Prosoma, dorsal view. B. Prosoma, ventral view. –C–D. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). C. Prosoma, dorsal view. D. Prosoma, ventral view. – E–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). E. Prosoma, dorsal view. F. Prosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468236/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">5G</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae, endites, labium, sternum and legs yellowish-orange (
<figureCitation box="[410,508,676,702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Figs 3D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[521,561,676,703]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[187,1396,396,1853]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. A–B. Caponina alejandroi sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3747). A. Prosoma, dorsal view. B. Prosoma, ventral view. –C–D. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). C. Prosoma, dorsal view. D. Prosoma, ventral view. – E–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). E. Prosoma, dorsal view. F. Prosoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468236/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">5H</figureCitation>
). Abdomen pale beige (
<figureCitation box="[840,969,676,702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
), covered by many dark, short setae, epigastric region pale orange. Spinnerets pale beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1398,776,838]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">MEASUREMENTS. Total length 3.65, carapace 1.34 long, 1.17 wide, 0.38 high, sternum 0.85 long, 0.80 wide, legs: I: 3.51; II: 3.35; III: 2.76; IV: 4.16, abdomen 2.25 long.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[188,1399,877,1079]" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">
MORPHOLOGY. Carapace flat with soft cuticle. Six eyes, AME the largest, dark, separated by about half their diameter, ALE pale translucent and smaller than AME, PLE pale translucent and smaller than ALE. Palpal femur with poorly developed dorsal tubercle and small prolateral stridulatory pick (
<figureCitation box="[1285,1383,947,974]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
); cymbium more than twice as long as tibia, with rounded tip, tegulum oval, with long, thin embolus, protruding ventrally from approximately middle surface of tegulum and directed anteriorly, with median expansion, widening tip and enlarged opening (
<figureCitation box="[744,868,1053,1079]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,234,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-15@8.[249,1338,265,1819]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. A–B, E–G. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. E. Left palp, retrolateral view. F. Left palp, ventral view. G. Left palp, prolateral view. – C–D, H–J. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. H. Left palp, retrolateral view. I. Left palp, ventral view. J. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A–D = 1.5 mm; E–J = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468230/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">Figs 3H–J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[880,952,1053,1079]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1319,768,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-165@9.[189,1398,761,1857]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Caponina bochalema sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3757). A. Left palp, retrolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, prolateral view. – D–F. Caponina huila sp. nov., ♂, holotype (IAvH-I 3761). D. Left palp, retrolateral view. E. Left palp, ventral view. F. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468234/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="99">4D–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
